---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Workflows', url: '/workflows' },
  { name: 'Medication Tracking', url: '/workflows/medication-tracking' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What medications can I track?',
    answer: 'Anything your vet prescribes or you administer. Antibiotics, anti-inflammatories, dewormers, hormones, sedatives, steroids, supplements, and more. The system comes with common medication templates for horses, dogs, cats, goats, sheep, and rabbits so you can get started fast.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does the withdrawal period countdown work?',
    answer: 'When you record a medication with a withdrawal period, BreederHQ calculates the clearance date automatically. The countdown updates every time you log a new dose, so the expiry is always based on the most recent administration, not just the start date. You\'ll see a red countdown badge that turns green when the animal is clear.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I track a multi-day treatment course?',
    answer: 'Yes. Create a treatment course with the dosage, frequency, and duration in the web app. Then check off each dose as you give it — including from the BreederHQ Mobile Companion app at the barn or kennel. The system tracks compliance (how many doses were given out of how many were prescribed) and reminds you when the next dose is due. Reminders push to the Mobile Companion so you get notified wherever you are.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does it handle batch medications like deworming?',
    answer: 'Yes. Select multiple animals, choose the medication, and log it once. Each animal gets its own treatment record with individual dose tracking. Common for deworming, fly control, and seasonal treatments.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I upload a vet invoice and have it populate automatically?',
    answer: 'Yes. Upload a prescription, vet invoice, or treatment plan (PDF or photo) and Scout AI extracts the medication name, dosage, frequency, and other details automatically. Review the pre-filled form and save. Scout also detects Coggins certificates and auto-updates your health records.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I share health records with my vet?',
    answer: 'Yes. Generate a full health report as a PDF, email it directly to your vet, or create a secure share link with a PIN code. Share links expire after 72 hours and lock after failed attempts.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does the Mobile Companion app support medication tracking?',
    answer: 'Yes — and this is a great example of how the BreederHQ Mobile Companion is built. The companion has a quick-log screen designed for on-the-go use in the barn, kennel, or wherever you are: see your active treatment courses, tap to log a dose, and move on. Push notifications remind you when the next dose is due. Full course management (adding new medications, editing courses, configuring schedules) lives in the web app, where setup work belongs. The companion is for in-the-moment capture; the web app is where you run things.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does it track controlled substances?',
    answer: 'Yes. Controlled substances are flagged in the system. Every dose is logged with who administered it and when, creating an audit trail. Prescription and lot/batch numbers are tracked.'
  }
];

const howTo = {
  name: 'How to Track Medications and Treatments',
  description: 'A step-by-step guide to logging medications, tracking treatment courses, monitoring withdrawal periods, and sharing health records for breeding animals.',
  steps: [
    { name: 'Add a medication course', text: 'Select the animal, choose from common medication templates or enter a custom medication. Set the dosage, route, frequency, and treatment duration. Add withdrawal period days if applicable.' },
    { name: 'Log each dose', text: 'As you administer each dose, tap "Log Dose" in the mobile or web app to record the date, time, and who gave it. The system tracks compliance, calculates the next due date automatically, and sends a push notification when the next dose is coming up.' },
    { name: 'Monitor withdrawal periods', text: 'For competition or sale animals, the withdrawal countdown updates with every dose. A red badge shows days remaining. When the withdrawal clears, the badge turns green.' },
    { name: 'Upload supporting documents', text: 'Attach prescriptions, vet invoices, or lab results to any treatment course. Upload a PDF or photo and Scout AI auto-extracts medication details.' },
    { name: 'Use group medication for herds or kennels', text: 'For group treatments like deworming, select multiple animals and log the medication once. Each animal gets individual tracking.' },
    { name: 'Share health records', text: 'Download a full health report PDF, email it to your vet, or generate a secure share link with PIN protection. Print a stall or kennel card for at-a-glance reference.' }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Medication Tracking That Keeps Up With You | BreederHQ"
  description="You already manage medications. BreederHQ keeps the record-keeping organized: treatment courses, automatic withdrawal countdowns, mobile push reminders, and shareable health reports for vets and buyers."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
  howTo={howTo}
>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Workflows</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Medication Tracking</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Section 1: What This Page Is About -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Medication Tracking That Keeps Up With You.</h1>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          You already manage medications for your animals, from routine deworming to post-surgical antibiotics to withdrawal compliance for competition or sale. BreederHQ keeps the record-keeping organized: treatment courses with dose-by-dose logging, automatic withdrawal countdowns, next-dose reminders that push to the BreederHQ Mobile Companion app, and shareable health reports for vets and buyers.
        </p>
      </aside>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        You know how to care for your animals. The challenge is keeping track of everything: multi-day courses, next-dose timing, and withdrawal periods for competition or sale. BreederHQ makes sure that record stays complete and accessible, without adding work to your day.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Breeders Search for This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">You already manage this. Here's what makes it complicated.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        You know what the animals need. The challenge is keeping everything straight across multiple animals and schedules:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Multi-day treatment courses with doses that need to be logged individually</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Different animals on different medications with different schedules</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Withdrawal periods that must be tracked accurately for competition eligibility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Barn staff who need to know what to give, when, and to whom</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Controlled substances that require proper documentation</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Vets who ask for a medication history and get "let me check my notes"</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        A missed dose, a miscounted withdrawal day, or a lost prescription record can mean a failed drug test, a disqualification, or a conversation with your vet or buyer you'd rather not have.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: How Breeders Usually Handle It -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">The tools you've been using</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Whiteboard in the barn or kennel</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            "Daisy - Bute 2x daily through Friday." Works until someone erases it, the schedule changes, or you have 15 animals on different meds.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Sticky notes and calendars</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            A note on the stall or kennel door. A reminder on your phone. A mark on the wall calendar. Three systems that don't talk to each other and none of them show dose-by-dose compliance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Vet invoices in a drawer</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The prescription is technically documented, somewhere in a stack of invoices. Finding it when you need it is the problem.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Spreadsheets</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            A column for date, a column for medication, a column for dosage. No connection to the animal's other records. No reminders. No withdrawal calculations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Memory</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            "I'm pretty sure she finished her antibiotics last week." "When did we last deworm the goats?" You know the info, but pulling it up on demand, weeks later, across multiple animals, is where memory stops being enough.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Where That Breaks Down -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Where those tools start to stretch thin</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Withdrawal periods get miscalculated</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            An animal gets a dose on the 1st, clearance is the 11th. Then something comes up and they get another dose on the 5th. Now clearance should be the 15th, but if you're counting from the first dose, you think they're clear on the 11th. That four-day gap can mean a positive drug test at a show or an unhappy buyer taking home an animal that hasn't cleared.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Dose compliance becomes invisible</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The vet prescribed 10 days of antibiotics. How many doses did the animal actually get? Did someone give Tuesday's dose? Did anyone log it? Without individual dose tracking, you're guessing about treatment completion.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Helpers and staff don't have the information</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You know what needs to happen. But you're not always there. The information needs to be accessible to whoever is doing the administering, not locked in your head or your personal notes app.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Health records are incomplete</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Your vet asks about medication history. You have vaccinations documented, but medications are scattered across invoices, text messages, and memory. The health picture is incomplete.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Group treatments have no audit trail</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You dewormed 30 animals on Saturday. Which product? What dosage? Which animals? If a withdrawal question comes up or someone has a reaction, the details matter.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: What a Correct System Looks Like -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">What it looks like when everything is connected</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Course-based treatment logging</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Each medication is a treatment course, not just a single entry</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Record the medication, dosage, route, frequency, and duration</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Check off individual doses as they're administered</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>See compliance: 7 of 10 doses given</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Automatic withdrawal calculation</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Withdrawal period recalculates from the most recent dose, not the first</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Live countdown showing days remaining until clearance</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Visual badge: red when active, amber when close, green when cleared</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Visible everywhere: animal list, animal detail, health tab, dashboard</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Next-dose reminders</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>System knows when the next dose is due based on frequency</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Push notifications to the BreederHQ Mobile Companion app so you get reminded wherever you are</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Overdue doses are flagged automatically</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Dashboard agenda shows upcoming medications alongside breeding milestones</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Group treatment support</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Apply the same medication to multiple animals at once</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Each animal gets its own treatment record for individual tracking</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Lot and batch numbers recorded for traceability</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Shareable health records</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Full health report as a downloadable PDF</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Email directly to your vet</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Secure share link with PIN protection</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Printable stall card with current medications and dosages</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: How BreederHQ Supports This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">How BreederHQ brings it all together</h2>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Create treatment courses with dosage, frequency, and withdrawal information in the web app. Log each dose as it's administered from your desk — or from the BreederHQ Mobile Companion app when you're at the barn or kennel. Withdrawal periods recalculate automatically with every dose. Next-dose reminders push to the Mobile Companion so you never miss one. Upload vet documents and let Scout AI extract medication details. Generate health reports and share them securely with your vet, trainer, or a buyer.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Built-in templates for common medications across horses, dogs, cats, goats, sheep, and rabbits. Group treatments for herd-wide or kennel-wide deworming. Controlled substance logging with audit trails. Printable stall or kennel cards with current medications. A medication history that's actually complete.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="https://accounts.breederhq.com/register?intent=breeder_dashboard" class="inline-block bg-white text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          Get Early Access
        </a>
        <a href="/workflows/genetics-and-health-testing" class="inline-block bg-transparent border-2 border-white text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] transition text-center">
          See health testing →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7: Who This Is For -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Built for breeders who:</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Show or compete and need accurate withdrawal tracking</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Have helpers or staff administering medications</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Manage multiple animals on different treatment schedules</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Need to share health records with vets, trainers, or buyers</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Do regular group treatments (deworming, fly control, seasonal protocols)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Want a complete medication history, not just vaccinations</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 8: Who This Is Not For -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">This might be overkill if:</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You have one or two pets and your vet handles everything</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You don't compete and don't need withdrawal tracking</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You rarely administer medications yourself</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 9: FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 faq-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Frequently asked questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What medications can I track?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Anything your vet prescribes or you administer. Antibiotics, anti-inflammatories, dewormers, hormones, sedatives, steroids, supplements, and more. The system comes with common medication templates for horses, dogs, cats, goats, sheep, and rabbits so you can get started fast.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How does the withdrawal period countdown work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>When you record a medication with a withdrawal period, BreederHQ calculates the clearance date automatically. The countdown updates every time you log a new dose, so the expiry is always based on the most recent administration, not just the start date. You'll see a red countdown badge that turns green when the animal is clear.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I track a multi-day treatment course?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Create a treatment course with the dosage, frequency, and duration in the web app. Then check off each dose as you give it — including from the BreederHQ Mobile Companion app at the barn or kennel. The system tracks compliance (how many doses were given out of how many were prescribed) and reminds you when the next dose is due. Reminders push to the Mobile Companion so you get notified wherever you are.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Does it handle batch medications like deworming?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Select multiple animals, choose the medication, and log it once. Each animal gets its own treatment record with individual dose tracking. Common for deworming, fly control, and seasonal treatments.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I upload a vet invoice and have it populate automatically?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Upload a prescription, vet invoice, or treatment plan (PDF or photo) and Scout AI extracts the medication name, dosage, frequency, and other details automatically. Review the pre-filled form and save. Scout also detects Coggins certificates and auto-updates your health records.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I share health records with my vet?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Generate a full health report as a PDF, email it directly to your vet, or create a secure share link with a PIN code. Share links expire after 72 hours and lock after failed attempts.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Does the Mobile Companion app support medication tracking?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes — and this is a great example of how the BreederHQ Mobile Companion is built. The companion has a quick-log screen designed for on-the-go use in the barn, kennel, or wherever you are: see your active treatment courses, tap to log a dose, and move on. Push notifications remind you when the next dose is due. Full course management (adding new medications, editing courses, configuring schedules) lives in the web app, where setup work belongs. The companion is for in-the-moment capture; the web app is where you run things.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Does it track controlled substances?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Controlled substances are flagged in the system. Every dose is logged with who administered it and when, creating an audit trail. Prescription and lot/batch numbers are tracked.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
